File: Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi. Twitter/Panyaza Lesufi JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department says it's halved the number of unplaced pupils for 2021. READ: Sadtu to challenge matric rewrite MEC Panyaza Lesufi has congratulated his team on social media, for reducing the number from 40,000 to 20,000 in a week. The department hopes to place the rest in the next week. Priority is given to children who live within the feeder zone closest to a school. Parents may object to placements within seven days of receiving the offer. There will also be a window for late applications, from 22 December to 22 January.